A loud explosion said to be a car bomb was heard in Somali capital Mogadishu on Wednesday noon, a day after a new security minister takes the oath of office.According to the Somalia's Information Minister Abdirahman Omar Osman Yarisow, the blast occurred at a cafeteria outside the ministry of youth and Sports in Mogadishu.A car with explosives detonated a Cafeteria outside the ministry of Youth &amp; Sports in #Mogadishu - there are casualties-- Abdirahman O. Osman (@engyarisow) April 5, 2017No group has yet claimed responsibility for the car bomb attack in Mogadishu, but Police blamed Al shabaab for the bombing.Developing story - More to come soon